[size=10pt][b]Making yourself admin[/b][/size]
Go into your login class and search for - [code]
if (p.username.equals(" [/code]
You should see this - [code]
if (p.username.equals("NAME")) { p.rights = 2; } [/code]
Explaining the code - [code]
if (p.username.equals("NAME")) { [/code]
That part of the code means that if the player's username is the name between the quotation marks, then - Code:
p.rights = 2;
That part of the code means that the player's rights will automatically be 2 when he/she logs in.
You can also add your own code for logging in as moderator - [code]
if (p.username.equals("NAME")) { p.rights = 1; } [/code]
Notice I changed the p.rights = 2; to p.rights = 1;. This means that if the player's username is the name between the quotation marks, then they will log in as a moderator.
These are the player rights for 508's. 0 = Normal player 1 = Moderator 2 = Administrator
[center] [b]Making the client connect to your ip[/b]
So first open your client and go to client.java. Then when it opens type Ctrl+f and search:
[code]beast43.no-ip.biz[/code]
Then when you get there change my servers ip to yours. Save the file the compile(build) and done.[/center]
[right][b]Making compile work (build)[/b]
Ok so whenever you see the .bat(build, compile, run, etc) Right click the .bat file and press edit. You will see something like this.
[code]@echo off "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_13\bin\javac.exe" ./files/*.java pause[/code]
Edit this into your jdk version
[code]jdk1.6.0_13[/code]
Edit the last two digits because mine is jdk 6 update 13. Yours may be jdk 6 update 6 it will look like this.
[code]jdk1.6.0_06[/code]
Then save and compile and your done!.[/right]
[b]Making Runserver work[/b]
Ok so when you run my server you dont use jdk you use jre.Jre is also what you use to play runescape and im going to show how you will get this.First off to get a free jre download go to of all places [url=http://java.com]java.com[/url] :0, Now when you download and install you will have you latest version.
Now do the same thing but edit run in the server it will look like this.
[code]@echo off cd ../bin "C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.6.0_06\bin\java.exe" palidino76/rs2/Server 43594 pause[/code]
Now edit this next thing to your jre version.
[code]jre1.6.0_13[/code]
Edit this to your jre version save and done.
[center][b]Enjoy my server any questions pm me[/b][/center]
